<!-- ============ ARTICLE ============ -->
<section class="sec" style="padding-top:40px">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="post-wrap post-body reveal">
<p>Multilingual video production supports brand expansion by letting a brand speak to new markets in their own language, which builds trust and lifts conversion in every region it enters. Studies show that 72% of consumers are more likely to buy from a website that communicates in their language. Viven provides video production services in multiple languages, helping brands communicate with global audiences while maintaining a consistent brand message across regions.</p><h2>The Importance of Multilingual Video</h2><p>Localized video content builds trust and increases conversion rates by speaking directly to potential customers in a way that resonates with them, rather than asking audiences to translate your message themselves. That difference matters most at the exact moment a prospect is deciding whether to trust a brand they've never heard of before.</p><h2>Viven's Multilingual Capabilities</h2><p>Viven offers multilingual scriptwriting, voiceovers, subtitles, and localization, ensuring that each video resonates with its intended audience while maintaining the brand's message across all markets. This applies equally to <a href={p("services/product-video")}>product demos</a>, <a href={p("services/how-to-video")}>explainer videos</a>, <a href={p("services/brand-video")}>corporate videos</a>, and customer testimonials.</p><h2>Case Study: Kanebo — Expanding Global Reach with Multilingual Videos</h2><p>Kanebo Cosmetics, a leader in the beauty and skincare industry, collaborated with Viven to produce a series of how-to videos for their Sensai product line. The goal was to provide clear instructions for product application across multiple regions. The videos were produced in multiple languages — including Chinese, Italian, French, English, German, and Russian — ensuring Kanebo could effectively reach its diverse international customer base.</p><p>By localizing the content, we ensured that each region received a personalized experience that resonated with its cultural nuances. The result was an engaging, effective set of videos that showcased the Sensai brand's elegance and functionality, building stronger connections with customers worldwide. Read more about <a href={p("blog/how-kanebo-elevates-luxury-through-cinematic-production-in-switzerland")}>how Kanebo elevates luxury through cinematic production in Switzerland</a>.</p><h2>Why Global Brands Trust Viven</h2><p>Accurate, culturally relevant localization, consistent brand messaging across markets, and real expertise producing video for international distribution — that's what makes multilingual video production work. If your product is complex as well as multilingual, see how <a href={p("blog/how-b2b-companies-simplify-complex-products-with-explainer-videos")}>B2B companies simplify complex products with explainer videos</a>, since the same clarity that works in one language needs to translate into every other one you localize into. Planning for multiple languages from the start, rather than translating a finished video afterward, is usually the more efficient path.</p><p><a href={p("contact")}>Start your multilingual video project with Viven</a> and reach every one of your markets in a voice they recognize as their own.</p>
    </div>
    <p class="post-service-note"><a href={p("services/brand-video")}>Want to see how this works in practice? Explore our brand video production.</a></p>
  </div>
</section>

